d 'PIDID': module to estimate Path-Integrated Difference-in-Differences 
d
d      pidid implements the Path-Integrated
d Difference-in-Differences framework: instead of comparing treated
d and control outcomes at    a single endline date, it treats the
d treatment effect as a trajectory				   
d		       tau(t) = c1(t) - c0(t)	 where c1(t) and
d c0(t) are the (group-mean) treated and control outcome paths over
d time, and integrates this gap over the    post-treatment window
d [t0, t1] using the trapezoidal rule to obtain the cumulative
d causal effect 						
d sigma = INTEGRAL_t0^t1 tau(t) dt    and the path-integrated
d Average Treatment Effect on the Treated, tau-bar = sigma / (t1 -
d t0).	For comparison, pidid also    reports the conventional
d static two-period DiD estimate, tau(t1) - tau(t0), which is
d computed only from the endpoints and can    be zero (or
d misleadingly small) whenever a transitory intervention's effect
d has fully decayed by t1, even though sigma remains	strictly
d positive.  See Salavi (2026) for the underlying theory and the
d endpoint-subtraction-bias result. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: repeated cross-sections
d KW: difference in differences
d KW: DiD
d KW: path-integrated
d KW: ATE
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260711
d
d Author: Comlan Apollinaire-Fabrice Salavi,  African School of Economics
d Support: email fsalavi@@africanschoolofeconomics.com
d
f pidid.ado
f pidid.sthlp
f pididplot.ado
f pididplot.sthlp
f test_pidid.do
